<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>Features that implement in C++ the GLSL specification as closely as possible. </para>

<para>The GLM core consists of C++ types that mirror GLSL types and C++ functions that mirror the GLSL functions.</para>

<para>The best documentation for GLM Core is the current GLSL specification, <link xlink:href="http://www.opengl.org/registry/doc/GLSLangSpec.4.20.8.clean.pdf">version 4.2 (pdf file)</link>.</para>

<para>GLM core functionalities require &lt;glm/glm.hpp&gt; to be included to be used. </para>
</section>
